data.text: @MarosSefcovic: I think we need a better quality of spending but keep open mind on how we finance the EU #EUMFF
EU Administration commissioner @MarosSefcovic now speaking at #EUMFF
Andersson: Invest in R&D and infrastructure to create a sustainable Europe in a number of areas #EUMFF
Andersson: Crisis can only be solved with openness and reform. EU budget should be a support for restructuring our economies #EUMFF
Andersson: Sweden today has one of the most competitive economies in the world because we have faced challenges in the past #EUMFF
Andersson: we have some bad experiences with financial transaction tax in Sweden in the 90s,  we should learn from history #EUMFF
Andersson: we are facing major challenges in Europe, demographics, debt, financial sustainability, good to have discussion here #EUMFF
Juergen Andersson from SE parliament now taking the floor #EUMFF
Wammen: #EUMFF will be high on the agenda for the DK presidency - we have a lot of work to be done!
Wammen: the presidency trio's single most important priority is the #EUMFF
Wammen: DK presidency will organise a similar conference in 2012 #EUMFF - for MPs and MEPs to meet with stakeholders.
Wammen: this is not the time for nationalism and free-riding, this is the time for unity! #EUMFF
New Danish Europe minister takes the scene for the EU presidency trio #EUMFF
Lamassoure: today national parliament have entered the European political scene #EUMFF
Lamassoure: the event is important but timing is not so good, many national budgets are being discussed and voted in October #EUMFF
Lamassoure: the only thing that doesn't flow freely in Europe is the political debate, it's broken into 27 parts #EUMFF
Lamassoure: We want to have full participation of the national parliaments on the EU budget #EUMFF
Lamassoure: Thanks for having political courage to organise this meeting, let this be a new start for how EU budget is decided #EUMFF
Now over to concluding remarks from Alain Lamassoure #EUMFF
Roper: The national parliaments HAVE been involved, but there could indeed be good reason to have more specialist meetings #EUMFF
Boege: This is one of the most productive conferences I have been part of #EUMFF
Boege: on development aid: we need to focus on the needs of the populations where we direct our aid #EUMFF
Boege: international competitiveness can only be secured if industry stays in Europe #EUMFF
Boege: on greening economy, EU 2020 strategy must be implemented, goals are clear and unambiguous #EUMFF
Comment: EC has provided lots of info but still need to explain the full impact of the proposal (like technical assessment) #EUMFF
Email Questions : How will #EUMFF and 2020 strategy ensure green economy and stable cohesion at the same time?
Comment: No time for blame game. Those who expect more from EU budget should not block it #EUMFF
Comment: What would be the cost of no EU? #EUMFF
Lamassoure Report:  http://t.co/GkDPnWmE #EUMFF
MEP Albrecht: Too late for discussing priorities. This is the time to read the text and then decide on the budget (applause) #EUMFF
Comment: We must stand up on the world stage together #EUMFF
Comment: After years of cohesion policy the case of Greece should not have happened - need for better impact assessments #EUMFF
Danish MEP: Read the back of the Lamassoure report!  #EUMFF
Danish MEP: We must keep an open mind, in DK it is easy to defend the paying to the new member states, but not for UK rebate! #EUMFF
Comment IT MP:  #EUMFF objective should enable European regions to grow together. #EUMFF
Comment: Highways to excellence do not seem to be reflected in budget proposal #EUMFF
Comment: growth and job creation are not opposing, both are necessary. You can't have single market without solidarity = EU budget #EUMFF
You can watch here http://t.co/3m7M7YYB #EUMFF
#EUMFF discussion now resuming
#EUMFF discussions to resume at 11.15 CET http://t.co/JzpIY7Hx
#EUMFF Now coffee break.
Roper: The Connecting Europe facility is a very important package, on Q1 greening means additional regulation #EUMFF
Roper: National parliaments already do already perform impact assessments #EUMFF
Böge: re Q1 growth under 2020 strategy looks into greener measures
Bóge: Political decisions  on EU level should be accompanied with a cost analysis like in German länder #EUMFF
Boege: impact assessment is an important issue, austerity and cuts do not mesh with EU decisions which mean increased spending #EUMFF
Q2: Why do we not look into direct EU tax and a real EU budget? #EUMFF
Q1: How to green direct payments? #EUMFF
Chair: Email questions have been sent in, I am now reading out two #EUMFF
Austrian MP: We need more flexibility, but it must be linked to transparency, clear rules are a must. We must continue the dialogue #EUMFF
Comment: #Lithuania has been progressing since 2004, but we must assess whether poorer EU countries have been able to catch up #EUMFF
Comment: we have to be able to measure how European measures like Frontex impact national budgets #EUMFF
Comment: we need better tools to monitor and compare local/national/European policies and budgets like they have in the US #EUMFF
Comment: there is a need to have a simpler and more transparent system to monitor EU revenue #EUMFF
Comment: Priorities must be clear and we should focus on added value and subsidiarity to avoid duplication #EUMFF
Comment to Cash: If member states do not want to pay for the EU objectives they must be honest and say they don't want them #EUMFF
Comment to Cash: EP has said that we must increase the EU budget if we are to meet the requirements of the Lisbon treaty #EUMFF
Roper: I am not sure there is a dispute between job creation and competitiveness. #EUMFF
Green MEP: EU 2020 strategy and green investments are crucial, we must concentrate more on common strategic investments #EUMFF
MEP Cash: We are in a crisis, but there is no recognition of where the money comes from. No possibility of UK parliament paying more #EUMFF
CZ foreign minister: by simplifying we can be more transparent #EUMFF
CZ foreign minister: we must maintain internal cohesion to be competitive #EUMFF
Swedish MEP: Better spending is an attractive alternative to more money #EUMFF
Swedish MEP: asks panel to reflect on the disagreement on CAP and cohesion funds between EU countries #EUMFF
Now comments and questions from the floor, Grabbe asks participants to be brief and only add points which were not made yesterday #EUMFF
Roper: on red tape: there are proposals for simplification within research programmes and we could look into the structural funds #EUMFF
Roper: We must think of spending well and wisely - therefore value added analysis is important in budget #EUMFF
Roper: proposals for national parliaments to do "value added checks" along with the existing subsidiarity checks  on EU actions #EUMFF
Roper: emphasis on dialogue between European institutions and national parliaments to develop common understanding on issues #EUMFF
Roper: Commission to look into conditionality of the structural funds #EUMFF
Roper: Ex: Structural funds have been vital in growth of Polish economy in recent years #EUMFF
Roper: we had a significant discussion on cohesion funds - especially who should benefit #EUMFF
Lord John Roper reports on Session 3: Adding Value: The EU Budget in Efficient Public Finances #EUMFF
Boege: altogether we had a very positive discussion and I hope we can continue it in more detail to have a proper dialogue on #EUMFF
Boege: lifelong learning programmes are also extremely important #EUMFF
Boege: On the relations with south and east neighbours, under #EUMFF we must be more ambitious
Boege: member states have very different views on CAP #EUMFF
Boege: Implementation must be streamlined and we should simplify the rues of the game #EUMFF
Boege: We must be watchful, the investment can have very positive effects on EU regions #EUMFF
Vast majority of speakers advocated for a strong cohesion policy #EUMFF
Boege: EU budget has been more stable than member states' budgets #EUMFF
#EUMFF session 2 had no big criticism on the EC proposal, but the devil is in the detail
Boege: Surprising that the discussion was taking place in a closed session, we should be able to explain EU budget to citizens #EUMFF
Boege: We are facing a new situation, great to see that so many partners are involved in the process of defining the priorities #EUMFF
11 member states were active in the debate in workshop 2 #EUMFF
Reimer Boege reports for Session 2: EU Expenditure: Spending Priorities for the Future #EUMFF
Cons, financial transaction tax: loss could be greater than revenues, it should be introduced globally first #EUMFF
Pro voices for financial transaction tax: similar things exist already in some EU countries. #EUMFF
Lots of voices both pro and con financial transaction tax in ws 1 #EUMFF
Debate in workshop 1:  willingness to investigate EC proposal @ASemetaEU #EUMFF
First up Report on Session 1: EU Revenue: The Future of Own Resources #EUMFF
Heather Grabbe, Open Society Institute opens the session #EUMFF
